Gene-commentary.Gene-commentary_text: Pax8 controls apical-basal follicular polarization and follicle formation through Cdh16.
the novel interplay between PAX8 and Neuropilin-2
The 5'-flanking region of the Wnt4 gene is responsive to Pax8. Pax8 modulates the expression of Wnt4 in thyroid cells.
Pax8 is required for the survival of differentiated epithelial cells and its expression levels are able to modulate the proliferation rate of such cells.
Distal regulation by Pax8 is supported by the interaction with chromatin remodeling factors such as CTCF and Sp1.
Transcriptome analysis highlighted that Pax8 is a key molecule for thyroid morphogenesis and differentiation
An unusual negative cross talk between Ras oncogene and the cyclic AMP pathway induces inactivation of the transcription factor Pax8.

thyrotropin-dependent thyroglobulin gene expression is stimulated by bacterial lipopolysaccharide at the transcriptional level by involving the transcription factors thyroid transcription factor-1 and paired box domain transcription factor 8
Pax8 and Smad3 interact and have a role in transforming growth factor-beta repression of the sodium/iodide symporter gene
glutathionylation of the first two cysteines has a regulatory role in paired domain binding
These results demonstrated that oxidoreductive modification of Cys-45 and Cys-57 via Ref-1 plays a role in redox regulation of Pax-8 in living cells.
Biased expression in Kidney (RPKM 165.1) and Uterus (RPKM 18.9)
